1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
What happens when water gets too much fertilizer?

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:08,000
Eutrophication occurs when nutrient runoff boosts algae growth in lakes and rivers.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:14,000
But here's the catch: too much algae blocks sunlight and oxygen for other life forms.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:19,600
This leads to dead zones where fish and plants can’t survive, impacting entire ecosystems.

5
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,400
Understanding eutrophication helps us combat water pollution and protect our water bodies.

6
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,200
Want to learn more about our planet?

7
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,200
Follow for more scientific insights!
